If you want to create your own cultures and societies, they will need a Con'''Planet''', or at least a local geography, to influence their beliefs, culture, and interactions. The materials provided in this section deal with how to create a realistic world for your peoples to inhabit.

Geoff Eddy has an excellent guide for creating planets[http://www.cix.co.uk/~morven/worldkit/index.html], which can be extremely helpful. Another website that deals with the scientific side of creating worlds is Anne Viau's [http://www.world-builders.org World-Builders.org].

The members at [http://www.unilang.org/ Unilang] started a wiki online called [http://planet.langwiki.info/ ConPlanet] allowing users to participate and interactively construct their con-nation alongside others in the conworld.

